# The repo gitignores `pulumi-language-python-exec` (it is normally a build artifact copied
# next to the CLI). Here it is deliberately VENDORED into the template — Python's run
# harness ships with the CLI, not the pip package, so a python program image needs its own
# copy (see the Dockerfile note). Re-include it so it is tracked and `pulumi new` scaffolds
# it. (The upstream fix is to ship the harness in the pip package, after which this and the
# vendored copy can go away.)
!pulumi-language-python-exec
